cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.HC 

The paper deals with the problem of blind or no-reference perceptual picture quality prediction, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves the use of deep learning architectures (cs.MM) and the collection and analysis of a large dataset (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper has implications for the social and streaming media industries, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper involves the prediction of picture quality, which could also be related to machine learning (cs.LG).
